<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-03-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-03-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="523" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">819.00/1168: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">South</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-03-06T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 6,
                                        1925—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>26. Your Nos. 31, March 4, 4 p.m., and 32, March 5, 7 p.m. Department
                            desires to congratulate you upon success of your efforts to compose
                            differences between Panaman officials and Indians and to commend you for
                            able handling of this difficult situation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>